{"serial": "21043", "department_serial": 22, "code": "MA3111", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "An Introduction to Mathematical Image Processing", "ch": "數學影像處理"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Yang, Suh-Yuh"], "ch": ["楊肅煜"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 2, "session": ["8"]}, "loc": {"building": "M", "room": "430"}}, {"time": {"week": 3, "session": ["7", "8"]}, "loc": {"building": "M", "room": "430"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "數學系", "en": "Department of Mathematics"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 1, "selected": 45, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "本課程主要介紹一些關於影像處理問題的數學研究。 它的兩個主要目標是：\n\n(1) 介紹適用於數位圖像處理的基本概念和方法，並為進一步研究奠定基礎。\n\n(2) 提供一些數學技術來研究影像處理中的幾個基本問題，例如如何恢復退化的圖像以及如何將其分割成有意義的區域等。\n\n***************\n萬一需要時視訊教學的 Google Meet連結：https://meet.google.com/sqs-sqhs-rkf", "en": "This course is concerned with the mathematical study of some image processing problems. Its two main objectives are\n\n(1) to introduce basic concepts and engineering approaches applicable to digital image processing and develop a further study foundation.\n\n(2) to provide some mathematical techniques for studying several fundamental questions in image processing, such as how to restore a degraded image and how to segment it into meaningful regions.\n\n***************\nDistance teaching and learning by Google Meet (if necessary): https://meet.google.com/sqs-sqhs-rkf"}, "outline": {"ch": "本課程預計將包含下列主題：\n(1) Basic concepts of digital image processing\n(2) Basic image processing operations in Matlab\n(3) Intensity transformations and spatial filtering\n(4) Image denoising\n(5) Image fusion\n(6) Image dehazing\n(7) Image contrast enhancement\n(8) Image inpainting\n(9) Image segmentation\n(10) Sparse dictionary learning for image processing\nCourse homepage: http://www.math.ncu.edu.tw/~syyang/", "en": "This course will cover the following topics:\n(1) Basic concepts of digital image processing\n(2) Basic image processing operations in Matlab\n(3) Intensity transformations and spatial filtering\n(4) Image denoising\n(5) Image fusion\n(6) Image dehazing\n(7) Image contrast enhancement\n(8) Image inpainting\n(9) Image segmentation\n(10) Sparse dictionary learning for image processing\nCourse homepage: http://www.math.ncu.edu.tw/~syyang/"}, "textbook": {"ch": "(1) [AK2002] G. Aubert and P. Kornprobst, Mathematical Problems in Image Processing: Partial Differential Equations and the Calculus of Variations, Second Edition, Springer Verlag, New York, 2002.\n\n(2) [CS2005] T. F. Chan and J. Shen, Image Processing and Analysis: Variational, PDE, Wavelet, and Stochastic Methods, Society for Industrial and Applied Mathematics, Philadelphia, 2005.\n\n(3) [TUM2019] D. Cremers, Computer Vision I: Variational Methods, Online Resources, Departments of Informatics ＆ Mathematics, Technical University of Munich, Germany, 2019/2020.\n\n(4) [GW2018] R. C. Gonzalez and R. E. Woods, Digital Image Processing, Fourth Edition, Pearson Education Limited, New York, 2018.", "en": "(1) [AK2002] G. Aubert and P. Kornprobst, Mathematical Problems in Image Processing: Partial Differential Equations and the Calculus of Variations, Second Edition, Springer Verlag, New York, 2002.\n\n(2) [CS2005] T. F. Chan and J. Shen, Image Processing and Analysis: Variational, PDE, Wavelet, and Stochastic Methods, Society for Industrial and Applied Mathematics, Philadelphia, 2005.\n\n(3) [TUM2019] D. Cremers, Computer Vision I: Variational Methods, Online Resources, Departments of Informatics ＆ Mathematics, Technical University of Munich, Germany, 2019/2020.\n\n(4) [GW2018] R. C. Gonzalez and R. E. Woods, Digital Image Processing, Fourth Edition, Pearson Education Limited, New York, 2018."}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "90%", "en": "90%"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n\n實習/實驗", "en": ["